## Set up Auth0 in Next.js

### 1. Create an Auth0 Application
- Go to https://manage.auth0.com → **Applications → Applications → Create Application**.
- Pick **Regular Web Application**, select **Next.js**.
- Note your **Domain**, **Client ID**, and **Client Secret**.
- Under **Settings → Application URIs** set:
  - **Allowed Callback URLs**: `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback`
  - **Allowed Logout URLs**: `http://localhost:3000`
- Add your production domain to both fields when you deploy.
- Save changes.

### 2. Install the SDK
```
npm install @auth0/nextjs-auth0
```

### 3. Environment variables
- Add to `.env.local` (never commit this file):
  ```
  AUTH0_SECRET='use-openssl-rand-hex-32-output-here'
  AUTH0_BASE_URL='http://localhost:3000'
  AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL='https://your-tenant.auth0.com'
  AUTH0_CLIENT_ID='your-client-id'
  AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET='your-client-secret'
  ```
- Generate `AUTH0_SECRET`:
  ```
  openssl rand -hex 32
  ```
- In production, set `AUTH0_BASE_URL` to your real domain (e.g., `https://myapp.com`).
- `AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL` must NOT have a trailing slash.

### 4. Create the catch-all route handler
- `app/api/auth/[auth0]/route.ts`:
  ```ts
  import { handleAuth } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0';
  export const GET = handleAuth();
  ```
- This single file registers four routes automatically:
  - `/api/auth/login` — redirects to Auth0 Universal Login
  - `/api/auth/logout` — ends the session and redirects home
  - `/api/auth/callback` — receives the Auth0 redirect and creates the session
  - `/api/auth/me` — returns the current user as JSON

### 5. Add UserProvider to the root layout
- `app/layout.tsx`:
  ```tsx
  import { UserProvider } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0/client';

  export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
    return (
      <html lang="en">
        <body>
          <UserProvider>{children}</UserProvider>
        </body>
      </html>
    );
  }
  ```
- `UserProvider` is required for `useUser()` to work in Client Components.

### 6. Access the session in Server Components
```tsx
import { getSession } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0';

export default async function ProfilePage() {
  const session = await getSession();
  if (!session) return <p>Not logged in.</p>;

  const { user } = session;
  return (
    <div>
      <img src={user.picture} alt={user.name} />
      <p>{user.name}</p>
      <p>{user.email}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 7. Access the session in Client Components
```tsx
'use client';
import { useUser } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0/client';

export function NavBar() {
  const { user, isLoading } = useUser();
  if (isLoading) return <span>Loading…</span>;
  if (!user) return <a href="/api/auth/login">Log in</a>;
  return (
    <div>
      <img src={user.picture} alt={user.name} />
      <a href="/api/auth/logout">Log out</a>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 8. Protect routes with middleware
- `middleware.ts` (project root):
  ```ts
  import { withMiddlewareAuthRequired } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0/edge';

  export default withMiddlewareAuthRequired();

  export const config = {
    matcher: ['/dashboard/:path*', '/settings/:path*', '/api/private/:path*'],
  };
  ```
- Unauthenticated requests are automatically redirected to `/api/auth/login`.
- For custom logic inside the middleware:
  ```ts
  import { withMiddlewareAuthRequired, getSession } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0/edge';
  import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

  export default withMiddlewareAuthRequired(async (req) => {
    const res = NextResponse.next();
    const session = await getSession(req, res);
    if (!session?.user.email_verified) {
      return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/verify-email', req.url));
    }
    return res;
  });
  ```

### 9. Protect API route handlers
```ts
import { withApiAuthRequired, getSession } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0';
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export const GET = withApiAuthRequired(async (req) => {
  const session = await getSession(req, new NextResponse());
  return NextResponse.json({ user: session!.user });
});
```

### 10. Login / logout links
```tsx
{/* Basic login */}
<a href="/api/auth/login">Log in</a>

{/* Redirect after login */}
<a href="/api/auth/login?returnTo=/dashboard">Log in</a>

{/* Logout */}
<a href="/api/auth/logout">Log out</a>
```

### 11. Roles and permissions (RBAC)
- In Auth0 Dashboard → **Actions → Flows → Login**, add a custom action:
  ```js
  exports.onExecutePostLogin = async (event, api) => {
    const ns = 'https://your-app.com';
    api.idToken.setCustomClaim(`${ns}/roles`, event.authorization.roles);
    api.accessToken.setCustomClaim(`${ns}/roles`, event.authorization.roles);
  };
  ```
- Read roles in Next.js:
  ```ts
  const session = await getSession();
  const roles = (session?.user['https://your-app.com/roles'] as string[]) ?? [];
  const isAdmin = roles.includes('admin');
  ```

### Common Errors & Fixes
- **`Discovery requests failing` / `ECONNREFUSED`** → `AUTH0_ISSUER_BASE_URL` is wrong. Must be `https://your-tenant.auth0.com` with no trailing slash.
- **`Invalid state` after login** → Callback URL mismatch. Add `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback` to Allowed Callback URLs in the Auth0 dashboard.
- **`useUser()` returns `{ user: undefined }`** → `UserProvider` is missing from `app/layout.tsx`.
- **Infinite redirect loop on protected pages** → The middleware `matcher` is too broad and includes `/api/auth/*`. Add a negative lookahead to exclude it:
  ```ts
  matcher: ['/((?!api/auth|_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)'],
  ```
- **`AUTH0_SECRET must be at least 32 characters`** → Generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`.
- **Roles not showing in session** → The Auth0 Action is not deployed or the namespace doesn't match. Check Actions → Flows → Login.
- **`withApiAuthRequired is not a function`** → Wrong import path. Use `import { withApiAuthRequired } from '@auth0/nextjs-auth0'` (not the `/edge` subpath).

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT expose `AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET` to the browser — never prefix it with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
- Do NOT write your own JWT verification — `@auth0/nextjs-auth0` validates tokens automatically.
- Do NOT call the Auth0 Management API from client-side code — use server-side functions only.
- Do NOT store the session in `localStorage` — the SDK uses secure HTTP-only cookies automatically.
- Do NOT include `/api/auth/:path*` in the middleware matcher — it creates an infinite redirect loop.
- Do NOT use Auth0 Social Connections (Google, GitHub) without enabling them in the Auth0 dashboard under Authentication → Social.
- Do NOT hardcode `AUTH0_BASE_URL` — it must be `http://localhost:3000` locally and your real domain in production.
